I ordered here because I was really craving pasta and their pasta looked really good, especially their Penne alla Vodka since it seems to be there most popular dish. So I place my order and decide to add a calzone on a whim. When I ordered it was close to the end of the night. When I received my order and tried my Penne alla Vodka with meatballs it was the driest pasta I have ever received. I assumed that it may have been because it was the end of the night and they ran out of sauce.  I called to ask for replacement and was met with a combative man who said when it left it was fine, and that no he would not replace the dish even on another day. This is after I stated that I would bring the dish myself after paying for delivery. He didn't care how the pasta was delivered and said that that's how they prepare it and I just don't have to order from them next time.  The one star, since that's the lowest I can give would be for the edible calzone.

My favorite restaurant for higher end bar food in the Lower East Side, especially South of Delancey. Their wings are by far my favorite in the LES, and I have had wings at dozens of bars in LES. Have never had the more premium Italian entrees but their heroes are really good too.  As far as the Bar aspect goes, affordable beers and cocktails and great place to actually watch a game with your pals at one of their big tables. I am in my mid 20s and also enjoy loud rowdy bars like Hair of the Dog or Side Bar but always found it annoying that there are so few bars in LES to actually watch a game without loud pop music blasting. Also they have shuffle board which is always a good time.  Overall I highly recommend grabbing a bucket of beers and a dozen hot wings here next time your in the area.

This is a great place. Their menu is absolutely delicious. Every single item they offer from appetizers to pizza or other main courses- it’s all so good. This is where you can find a pizza to die for that has Brussels sprouts and pancetta or bacon and the perfect cheesy pizza. Penne vodka.... YUM.... Pink pizza.... perfection and kids love it. Their fries are perfectly delicious. They know acknowledge my kids with delight each time we are there and they just love that. They are the most kid friendly restaurant I’ve ever experienced. They let my little guy hand the wait staff the credit card to pay the bill, and take the receipt. It’s a nice neighborhood place that offers great service and such a kind and friendly environment. Great family place with good seating and room for a stroller.  The only time I’ve ever been upset with Saluggis is when I have ordered on seamless. My favorite thing to get here is the spinach salad with blue cheese and pancetta... when I order it in seamless the delivery is wrong every time. But this salad as well as the Italian chickpea salad are just delicious.
